The article is a transcript of a speech delivered by President Joe Biden at the University of Connecticut in Storrs, Connecticut. In his speech, Biden discusses the life and legacy of Senators Thomas Dodd and Chris Dodd, highlighting their commitment to human rights and dignity. He emphasizes the importance of treating all people with respect and decency. Biden also speaks about the need to defend and promote human rights both domestically and internationally. He mentions specific human rights issues, such as the treatment of Uyghurs in Xinjiang, the Rohingya crisis in Burma, and the abuses in Northern Ethiopia. Biden emphasizes the role of the United States in leading by example and working with allies to uphold democratic values and human rights. He concludes by urging the students in the audience to pursue their dreams and make a positive impact on the world.